[Student "S"]
{WEST has a decent Limit Raise, and EAST tries RKC Blackwood.

WEST replies to the 4NT bid with 5\D, zero or three Keycards. 
So which is it, zero or three?

Pretty simple - since EAST holds three Keycards himself WEST can hardly have three also since there 
are only five total. She must have zero and EAST signs off at 5\H.}

